-- Australian Leader Gillard to Hold Meeting With Obama at Japan APEC Summit
-- B y   G e m m a   D a l e y
-- 2010-10-29T01:27:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/australian-leader-gillard-to-hold-meeting-with-obama-at-japan-apec-summit.html
Australian Prime Minister  Julia Gillard  will have her first bilateral talks with U.S. President
 Barack Obama  during the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation summit
in November in Japan.  They will discuss Australia’s involvement in Afghanistan,
economic and trade issues as well as North Korea at the Nov. 13
meeting in Yokohama, according to an e-mailed transcript of a
White House briefing.  Gillard’s Labor Party formed a minority government after
the Aug. 21 election delivered the closest result for 70 years.
Australia has 1,550 soldiers in Afghanistan and Gillard has said
the nation may have a presence there for the next decade.  Gillard, who  told  the Australian Broadcasting Corp. on Oct.
5 that “foreign policy is not my passion” will attend the East
Asia summit hosted by the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
in Vietnam this weekend before heading to Indonesia and Malaysia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Gemma Daley  in Canberra at 
 gdaley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
